data.name: label5.Text
data.value: Gameplay begins with betting. Once bets are placed, the first hand is dealt. The player can choose to hold zero, one, or more cards from the hand. Next, cards that are not held are replaced with cards from the deck. Finally, the player will be rewarded according to strength of hand. If a winning hand is not achieved, the player will not receive a reward.

data.name: label7.Text
data.value: Betting begins before the first hand is dealt. The player can choose to bet between 1 and 5 credits, with 5 credits corresponding to the greatest winnings. Each row in the payoff table corresponds to the number of credits that are bet. So, the greatest amount of credits a player can win is 4000, which is earned by betting 5 credits and drawing a royal flush.
